Exercise 15.2: How does the protected access specifier differ from
private?

Answer:
Protected - allows access for base class, friend function and  derived classes access.
Private - allows access for base class and friend function.


Exercise 15.4: Which of the following declarations, if any, are incorrect?
Explain why.
class Base { ... };

(a) class Derived : public Derived { ... };
(b) class Derived : private Base { ... };
(c) class Derived : public Base;
Answer:
a)Incorrect since a class can't derive from itself.
b)Incorrect, this is a definition not declaration.
c)Incorrect, derived class is declared like any other class, it includes the class name but not its derivation list.

