Exercise 15.32: What happens when an object of type Query is copied,
moved, assigned, and destroyed?

Answer:
When a Query is copied, moved, assigned or destroyed the synthesized versions will be called since it doesn't have any of
the operations overridden.

Exercise 15.33: What about objects of type Query_base?

Answer:
Since Object is derived from Query_base it will call that derived class type object's own copy control which in turn
will call the  synthesized version of the copy control of Query_base.

